WHO   — The Skolnik Name — the Raskolnikov nod
WHAT  — The whole adaptation compressed into a name: the one piece of Dostoevsky's intellect the film keeps, sewn into a surname like a footnote.
WHERE — CPS · Crime + Punishment in Suburbia  Framework inputs: Crime + Punishment in Suburbia (2000)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film, having dropped the philosophy, points back to it the only way it can — by naming the girl after the man whose theory it left out.
HOW   — By a single syllable swapped out of ‘Raskolnikov,’ legible to anyone who's read the book.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the whole of Dostoevsky the movie kept — a surname; read me and go find the head the film left on the page.

